metadata.name: Flight rhythm #10
metadata.description:
I watched the crowds of birds flying together from the window. It was amazing. They all spun in a circle and flew to the next at the end of the open circle. It was an endless rhythm of their mass flight that I had been immersed in for a while. The endless rhythm! This excerpt reminded me of Robert Delaunay's masterpiece, "The rhythm." 
Yeah, circles in circles and a wavy motion with a repetitive rhythm was my choice to create this artwork, Because the circle is a symbol of movement.
This work is designed in 50 editions, each with a different color would give you the pleasure of watching the flight.
note: "my first experience of NFT works"
"Stay tuned for the next collections"

metadata.name: Totalistic Cellular Automata #18
metadata.description:
Totalistic Cellular Automata is a work celebrating my appreciation and love for 1D Cellular Automata. In this piece there are many different rules and rulesets which dictate how the cells will behave. Totalistic cellular automata is a type of cellular automata where the total or average values of cells in a neighborhood are what the rules depend on.

Clicking the image continues or pauses the generation.

There are 4 dimension sizes, 4 possible states, 52 possible rulesets, and 55 colorways. 

This generator was inspired by the works and discoveries of Stephen Wolfram and “RGB Elementary Cellular Automata” by Ciphrd which will always have a special place in my heart.

JohnWow(2022)

metadata.name: Antiflow #250
metadata.description:
"Opposites are not contradictory but complementary." - Niels Bohr

The concept of yin and yang is an ancient philosophy about how opposing forces are not only complementary but actually give rise to each other. This idea reverberates through nature, art, and life itself. Now it is at the heart of modern physics. Perhaps this is a fundamental law of nature baked into the very fabric of existence.

Antiflow is an exploration of how balanced complexity can arise from chaos by harnessing the dynamic interplay of opposing forces. To that end we were inspired to create this wildly unique set by mixing modern physics concepts with abstract expressionism and retro 3D primitives.

The aspect ratio is 3:2 to facilitate poster size prints and device wallpapers. Results are presented without borders, noise, or other effects to allow for maximum detail. Feel free to rotate in whatever direction you choose for the best display.

Press "S" to save at a higher definition.
tags: chaos opposites retro expressionist antiparticle flow p5js

metadata.name: Phantoms #206
metadata.description:
Phantoms is a series of hazy memories of distant places. Some tranquil, others sinister, each scene is as much defined by what is revealed as by what remains unseen.

In this collection I aim to juxtapose hard and soft. Blocky shapes form the core of the compositions. Upon these surfaces, soft textures appear to flow and drip over the sides. Varying levels of opacity, lighting, and fog effects further soften the scenes to create an atmospheric, dream-like quality. By remaining semi-abstract, each of the color palettes are given the space to influence the mood dramatically.

metadata.name: WEIRD FISHES 7, 8, 9 and 10 #21
metadata.description:
Final drop of the WEIRD FISHES serie

Weird Fish 7 - The Bulldog Clownfish (35% probability)
Weird Fish 8 - The Unicorn Fish (30% probability)
Weird Fish 9 - The Guppy Fish (20% probability)
Weird Fish 10 - The Pterois Volitans (15% probability)

These are the 7th, 8th, 9th and 10th in a collection of 10 fish
Each drop in this serie have less possible iterations compared to the previous one, making these new fish the most rare!



This token features:
Many different coral reefs in various colours
Fishes in different sizes and colours
Small fish banks in random number and colour
Random bubbles
Random speed
Perline noise plancton in different quantities size and colour
